The paper discusses a technique for improving query performance in RDF graphs, which falls under the category of database systems (cs.DB). The use of signature-based pruning also involves machine learning and artificial intelligence techniques (cs.AI), as well as information retrieval (cs.IR) and deep learning (cs.DL) methods. The paper also discusses the underlying graph structure and complexity of queries, which are relevant to the field of machine learning and data mining (cs.LG).
